# Task: Unit Tests for SearchInput

## Objective

Add comprehensive unit tests to prevent regression of the race condition fix.

## Test File Location

`__tests__/unit/search-input.test.tsx` (create if doesn't exist)

## Test Cases

### 1. Rapid Typing Preserves All Characters
```typescript
it('preserves all characters during rapid typing', async () => {
  const onChange = vi.fn()
  render(<SearchInput onChange={onChange} />)

  const input = screen.getByRole('textbox')

  // Simulate rapid typing (10ms between keystrokes)
  await userEvent.type(input, 'software', { delay: 10 })

  expect(input).toHaveValue('software')
})
```

### 2. Debounce Fires After Delay
```typescript
it('calls onChange after debounce delay', async () => {
  vi.useFakeTimers()
  const onChange = vi.fn()
  render(<SearchInput onChange={onChange} debounceMs={300} />)

  const input = screen.getByRole('textbox')
  await userEvent.type(input, 'test')

  expect(onChange).not.toHaveBeenCalled()

  act(() => { vi.advanceTimersByTime(300) })

  expect(onChange).toHaveBeenCalledWith('test')
})
```

### 3. Controlled Value Sync Does Not Interrupt Typing
```typescript
it('does not reset input when controlled value catches up', async () => {
  const { rerender } = render(<SearchInput value="" onChange={vi.fn()} />)

  const input = screen.getByRole('textbox')
  await userEvent.type(input, 'abc')

  // Simulate parent updating controlled value (as would happen from URL)
  rerender(<SearchInput value="ab" onChange={vi.fn()} />)

  // Input should NOT be reset to "ab" - user's "c" should be preserved
  expect(input).toHaveValue('abc')
})
```

### 4. Clear Button Works
```typescript
it('clears input when clear button clicked', async () => {
  const onChange = vi.fn()
  render(<SearchInput value="test" onChange={onChange} />)

  const clearButton = screen.getByRole('button', { name: /clear/i })
  await userEvent.click(clearButton)

  expect(screen.getByRole('textbox')).toHaveValue('')
})
```

### 5. External Clear Syncs Correctly
```typescript
it('syncs when parent clears value', async () => {
  const { rerender } = render(<SearchInput value="test" onChange={vi.fn()} />)

  expect(screen.getByRole('textbox')).toHaveValue('test')

  rerender(<SearchInput value="" onChange={vi.fn()} />)

  expect(screen.getByRole('textbox')).toHaveValue('')
})
```

## Test Utilities Needed

```typescript
// Helper to simulate realistic typing speed
async function typeRapidly(element: HTMLElement, text: string) {
  for (const char of text) {
    await userEvent.type(element, char, { delay: 0 })
    // Small delay between characters to allow state updates
    await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 5))
  }
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] All 5 test cases pass
- [ ] Tests run in under 5 seconds
- [ ] No flaky tests (run 10x to verify)
- [ ] Coverage for SearchInput component > 80%

